				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="4">Gordon stops by the general EQ forums</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/1/2000-3:13:51 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=288807"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035997.html">PLEASE PUT BACK FEMALE REST ANIMATION!!</a></B><P>

You had it in there once before, please put back the female resting animation!<P>

<B>We don't like the way that the stance looks. Perhaps we'll go through and revisit it in the future, but no promises at present.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036095.html">Abashi please....</a></B><P>

Please look into the recent pet changes. I know you say only a proc modifier was changed, but WAY too many people are noticing big changes in pet offense/defense.<P>

<B>I did some testing, specifically with 49th level necro and mage pets, and compared them to my results from early this year. Both pets were naked, no buffs, and both had similar results to what occurred earlier this year with the same tests. <P>

I'm not sure what I can say to put everyone's concerns to rest. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036106.html">Please answer these questions. Abashi/Absor</a></B><P>

Did you say that DEX was much lower for pets now ?<P>

<B>No. The Dex of pets is not lower than it ever was. What is lower is their proc percentage chance based off of that dex. It used to roll of the NPC table and now rolls of a PC table. </B><P>

Does DEX affect the fact that an Attack lands, and also affects damage ?<P>

<B>No. It does not.</B><P>

Did you also lower AGI on pets now ?<P>

<B>We have not lowered any pet stats.</B><P>

Now... I have the same example in about 4 or 5 threads of a battle with a blue croc in other posts. My pet was getting hit for more damage, and was hitting less often for less damage. Coincidence ? How can 2 hours of trying the same thing be coinsidence ? I played in Oasis for a few hours prior patch and it wasn't that way.<P>

<B>You aren't dealing with constants when fighting things in Oasis. NPCs have level ranges. Pets have level ranges. Hit and miss percentages have ranges. Damage dealt and damage taken have ranges. A combination of good or bad rolls on one side or another can make it appear that things have changed in one way or another, but they haven't.<P>

I've been back and forth with several programmers over the past two weeks about this, in addition to running my own tests and having them run theirs. The only determination that we've made is that aside from the procing weapon issue, which I think people understand as a bug fix at this point, is that they have not changed. <P>

Perhaps the best way I can "prove" to everyone that they haven't changed is by pointing to the lack of people with concrete figures here. When we *really* change something, the board is flooded with a certain type of player making complaints. These are the people who log and parse everything, and can find changes with the combat engine down to single percentage points. Those people are not here. What we have are people who "get the feeling that" something is different.<P>

Trust me, if there was something different with the basic way pets were in combat, there would be players here with exact figures explaning exactly what changed.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036147.html">Endless new threads on the same topic: Why they hurt everyone...</a></B><P>

<I>It's simple. People go looking for "official" posts on an issue, and instead of having to look at two or three, they have to filter through dozens. The ones with the official replies are missed and end up down on page 10, while post after post gets bumped to the front page asking "Why are you ignoring this". Please, do everyone a favor and use the search tool to look and see if there's a post on your issue that may have been answered already. I've personally answered 3 of these pet posts today, and read at least half a dozen threads asking why we haven't responded to the issue since then. <P>

-Gordon</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036148.html">Verant refuses to give players a clue...</a></B><P>

as to what date SoV will actually go live.
I'm not talking what date the game will ship or be in stores. What day will SoV be live ?<P>

<B>Providing that retailers don't sell it too soon, it will be live on the servers by the time you get home from the store with your box.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="5">Alan on various things EverQuest</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/1/2000-3:12:36 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=288799"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036115.html">absor a few questions</a></B><P>

Belgariad wrote: "Mage Epic. There was some talk from alan that you might change the cloak from quillmane. If that is planned than i would like you to hear this suggestion in how it would drop. Have a new NPC in a mid level zone (that doesn't have a lot of newbies that would try and ninja the items). Have that NPC ask for the two quest focus items that wasn't requested in the epic (the torch and the stien). When you turn these 2 items in it would spawn a high level elemental (like the one in Burning woods for cleric epic quest) that a 4 to 5 groups could kill with some trouble. The elemental would drop the cloak used in the Air portin of this quest."<P>

<B>If there is a change to the cloak drops, it will probably not be anything nearly that dramatic.</B><P>

"Next concern in the mage epic is that so far nobody on any server has gotten burning ember and can prove that they got it. People has been killing every wurm countless times that are a short jounery from skyfire. Is there any way for you to get EsterTheTester to go to a live server and let her try and get it. "the burning embers from a notable member of wurm-kind who can be found a short journey from here " this is the only clue to burning ember and there are a lot of notable members of wurm-kind near skyfire. 
Dirt of underfoot a stealf enhacement and than a stealf nerf. It was put into the game on the patch before thanksgiving and it dropped every time when you killed silxen the mighty in BW. About 5 days later BW was patched by itself and mages thought that it was to fix the noexesting burning embers but what happened was that the dirt of underfoot now is a very rare drop."<P>

<B>Burning Embers were, in fact, goofed up severely. They are in game now, I've seen them myself.</B><P>

