<B>When/if that happens, keep in mind that it will be moved to an equally difficult opponent. Such a move will probably not make the item easier to obtain. I've got no estimate for the timing of such a move, I can't even promise you that it will happen for sure.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036114.html">Just a heads up Verant - This is WHY people spam your boards</a></B><P>

It's worth the headache for them. Even the most belly-aching posters sometimes post good ideas. Verant then comes though and cherry picks the good ideas and implements them. Many good improvements came from suggestions on this board. I am sure that Absor and Abashi may hate their jobs some times, but were else can they get this many people that have ideas to improve their product. <P>

<I>Very well said Orm.<P>

Good ideas do come from these boards, and they are often the first place that we get some real-time feedback on problems that pop up from time to time. <P>

-Gordon</I><P>

<B>We don't hate our jobs!<P>

And I do my best to revisit posts and see what responses my comments earn. That's the essence of communicating. Spamming is like yelling at someone repeatedly to get attention. It doesn't mean that the person yelling isn't in need of help, but it sure doesn't make for effective communication.<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="6">Friday morning forum bits from Gordon</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/1/2000-12:51:34 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=288616"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[2]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036036.html">VERANT IGNORES EVEN RESONABLE REQUESTS.</a></B><P>

I guess I am a little upset at the poor service Verant customer service offers. Today I called and spoke with a very nice customer service representative that was very helpfull and a nice change from what I experience online with the GM's. I was calling because I wanted to be moved off of the server Solusek Ro. <P>

<B>This issue has come up a number of times and I've explained our position. We do not do ad hoc moves between servers. <P>

The sheer number of requests along this line that would come in would keep a staff three times our size busy 24 hours per day. Remember that there are over 300K people playing EverQuest, and number of characters are well into the millions. <P>

Now it has been suggested that we should charge for the service, but we feel that server communities are important, and that characters should have to live with their reputations.<P>

The short of it is that it is not economically feasible to do ad hoc moves, and even if we were to set it up so that it was, we'd still be dealing with the issue of the importance of server communities.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036041.html">We're locking threads....</a></B><P>

<I>Posts that are monopolizing the front page with a particular issue are being locked. That's clearly defined as against the rules in the board FAQ. Chances are that if an issue is that important it's already been addressed a number of times. The mage pets issue that's currently hot falls under this definition. We've announced exactly what changes were made, and no changes other than what we've told you have been made. We've continued "looking into" the issue over the past several days and can find absolutly nothing to suggest that any other changes have occurred. If something changes we'll let you know, but until then the issue is closed.<P>

Posts that are rude or antagonistic are being locked. See the FAQ.<P>

Posts asking why threads are being locked are being locked. Posting threads of this nature is essentially spamming the boards, so please don't do it.<P>

Thank you for your cooperation,<P>

-Gordon</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036023.html">Verant nerfs players, players now proc PlayEQ 300% less</a></B><P>

So Verant how many players do you lose of your claimed 300,000 subscribers every nerf patch?
While we're at it, let us all reflect on all the patches implemented since EQ came out 2 years ago. I have been playing for a year and a half myself so i'll base my guesses below on that time period. I would guess the following (and they are approximations):<P>

<B>My first instinct was to pass this post up because it uses the "pull numbers of out thin air and call them facts" method of debate. The only way to "address" a post of this nature is to spend a day researching all of the correct numbers for the purpose of showing what really is fact. That would take too much time and only validate this method as a way to get a response, which is why we pass these posts up.<P>

That said, there is one claim I would like more information on:<P>

What server is this that you play on that you've noticed a 200-300 player drop at peak over the past year? <P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="7">Sacking of Highkeep Report from Lady Dae</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[12/1/2000-12:51:08 PM]</font>
